## COMPLETE CODE - Copy everything below this line and paste into Bolt.new

I need to build a Message Management System with React + TypeScript + Vite + Tailwind CSS + Supabase.

The database already exists with these tables: text_messages, email_messages, categories, email_categories, sales_funnels, funnel_content_assignments.

Use these exact Supabase credentials:
- VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://tpgenpsfhlochdccpbje.supabase.co
- VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJzdXBhYmFzZSIsInJlZiI6InRwZ2VucHNmaGxvY2hkY2NwYmplIiwicm9sZSI6ImFub24iLCJpYXQiOjE3NjE3MTQ1MzMsImV4cCI6MjA3NzI5MDUzM30.BE4kH2mP2XBoZtDMJdL4X9eP9Rheynt4oIQdYkWEJBs

Requirements:

1. Create a beautiful, modern UI with:
   - Two main tabs: "Messages" and "Categories"
   - Four message type filters: SMS Broadcast, SMS Funnel Content, Email Broadcast, Email Funnel Content
   - Color scheme: orange for SMS Broadcast, emerald for SMS Funnel Content, blue for Email Broadcast, cyan for Email Funnel Content
   - Search by content name (text input with search icon)
   - Filter by category (dropdown)
   - Message table showing: Content Category, Content Name, Subject/Content, Created Date, Sent Date/Sales Funnels, Actions
   - Action buttons: Send (broadcast only), Edit, Copy, Delete

2. Message Management Features:
   - Create new messages (modal with form)
   - Edit existing messages (same modal)
   - Copy/duplicate messages (auto-adds "(Copy)" to name)
   - Delete messages (with confirmation)
   - Send broadcast messages (updates sent_date)
   - Broadcast modal for selecting and sending messages
   - Show funnel assignments for funnel content messages (badges with funnel names)

3. Category Management Features:
   - Separate tabs for SMS Categories and Email Categories
   - Create new categories (inline form)
   - Edit categories (inline form)
   - Delete categories (with confirmation)
   - Display category name and description

4. Technical Requirements:
   - Use @supabase/supabase-js for database operations
   - Use lucide-react for all icons
   - Use Tailwind CSS for all styling
   - TypeScript types for all data structures
   - Proper error handling with console.error and alerts
   - Loading states with spinner
   - Responsive design
   - No placeholder content - use real data from Supabase

5. Data Models:
   - TextMessage: id, context_category, content_name, content, message_type ('broadcast' | 'funnel_content'), created_date, sent_date, created_at, updated_at
   - EmailMessage: id, context_category, content_name, subject, content, message_type ('email_broadcast' | 'email_funnel_content'), sent_date, created_at
   - Category: id, name, description, created_at, updated_at
   - SalesFunnel: id, name, description, created_at, updated_at
   - FunnelContentAssignment: id, funnel_id, message_id, created_at

6. Sorting Rules:
   - Broadcast messages: Sort by sent_date (pending first, then newest sent first)
   - Funnel content: Sort by category name, then content name

7. UI Details:
   - Header: "Message Management" with MessageCircle icon
   - Gradient background: from-gray-50 to-gray-100
   - White cards with shadows and rounded corners
   - Hover effects on all interactive elements
   - Modal overlays with backdrop
   - Table with alternating row hover states
   - Colored filter buttons with active states
   - Form inputs with focus rings
   - Disabled button states for loading

Build this exactly as specified with no shortcuts or placeholder content. Use the existing Supabase database - do not create tables.
